5 Insightful Analyst Questions From Procter & Gamble’s Q1 Earnings Call
items.description: Procter & Gamble’s first quarter results were met with a negative market reaction, as management pointed to consumer and retail volatility in the U.S. and Europe as significant headwinds. CFO Andre Schulten explained that “the consumer has been hit with a lot, and that's a lot to process,” referencing shifting retail traffic, cautious spending, and changes in purchasing channels.
